org.codehaus.preon.el
Interface Expression<R,C>

Type Parameters:
R - The type of value returned when evaluating this expression.
C - The type of context to which this expression applies.
All Superinterfaces:
Descriptive
All Known Subinterfaces:
Node<T,E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractNode, ArithmeticNode, BooleanLiteralNode, BooleanOperatorNode, ConvertingNode, ExpressionNode, IntegerNode, IntegerReferenceNode, ReferenceNode, RelationalNode, StringNode
public interface Expression<R,C>
extends Descriptive

An object encapsulating an expression, with the ability to evaluate itself against an external context, and the ability to describe itself against a certain external context.

Here are some of the typical things you might expect to get when describing the expression in human-readable language: 

 car.tyre.weight > 3
     "the weight of the car's tyre is bigger than 3"
 map.settings.version < 650
     "the version of the map's settings is smaller than 650"
 body.weight = 70
     "the body's weight equals 70"
 body.weight.max = 80
     "the max of the body's weight equals 80"

Author:
Wilfred Springer
